  "local_port": 49618,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "Creating a pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3 can be a lot of fun and quite effective in both PvE and PvP. Here are the essential stats and considerations for optimizing your pyromancer build:\n\n### Key Stats to Focus On:\n\n1. **Intelligence (INT)**: \n   - While it doesn't scale with pyromancy damage, having some points in INT can increase the power of certain pyromancies and also allow you to use certain spells more effectively.\n\n2. **Faith (FTH)**: \n   - Similar to INT, this governs certain pyromancies and can enhance your power in specific spells.\n\n3. **Attunement (ATT)**: \n   - This determines the number of spell slots you have available. You typically want at least 10 Attunement to have access to several pyromancies.\n\n4. **Endurance (END)**: \n   - Vital for stamina management. You'll want enough endurance to roll effectively and use your weapons/spells without running out of stamina.\n\n5. **Vitality (VIT)**: \n   - This is important for your overall health, allowing you to survive engagements. Aim for a healthy amount to ensure you can take a few hits.\n\n6. **Dexterity (DEX)**: \n   - If you're using a weapon that scales with Dexterity, consider putting points here. Dexterity also reduces casting time for spells, which can make a difference in fast-paced encounters.\n\n7. **Strength (STR)**: \n   - This is mostly secondary for pyromancers unless you're using a specific weapon requiring Strength.\n\n### Suggested Level Distribution:\n\nA typical inflection point for a pyromancer build might look something like this at SL120:\n\n- **Strength:** 16 (if you want to use heavier weapons)\n- **Dexterity:** 30 (for casting speed and weapon use)\n- **Intelligence:** 30 (to boost pyromancy damage)\n- **Faith:** 30 (for the same reason as Intelligence)\n- **Endurance:** 25 (enough to wear armor and roll effectively)\n- **Vitality:** 10-15 (depending on how much you want to weigh)\n\n### Recommended Weapons and Pyromancies:\n\n- **Weapons**: \n  - **Chaos Blade**: A solid melee option if you go more Strength/Dexterity.\n  - **Fire-infused weapons**: Can also benefit from your pyromancy scaling.\n  - **Pyromancer's Parting Flame**: A great talisman for casting pyromancies effectively.\n\n- **Pyromancies**:\n  - **Fireball / Great Fireball**: Good for general use.\n  - **Chaos Fireball**: High damage and wide area of effect.\n  - **Flame Whip**: Useful for close combat situations.\n  - **Fire Surge**: A rapid-fire pyromancy, good for pressure.\n  - **Black Flame**: Deals damage over time and is a great option in PvP.\n\n### Equipment:\n\n- **Pyromancer's Flame**: Your main tool for casting spells.\n- **Armor**: Consider a balance of weight and poise. Favor lighter armor for better mobility unless you can find a good balance.\n- **Rings**:\n  - **Bellowing Dragoncrest Ring**: Boosts sorcery (also benefits pyromancy).\n  - **Great Swamp Ring**: Specifically boosts fire damage.\n  - **Ring of Favor**: For increased HP, stamina, and equip load.\n  - **Young Dragon Ring**: Increases damage of sorceries and pyromancies.\n\n### Tips:\n\n- Mix pyromancies with melee damage for the best versatility.\n- Always keep an eye on your spell slots and plan your loadout according to your play style.\n- Use the environment to your advantage, especially in PvP scenarios.\n\nEnjoy your journey as a pyromancer in Dark Souls 3! Adjust your stats and strategies based on your preferences and the challenges you face.",
